Install and load required libraries

if (!requireNamespace("ggmap", quietly = TRUE)) install.packages("ggmap")
if (!requireNamespace("ggplot2", quietly = TRUE)) install.packages("ggplot2")
if (!requireNamespace("ggspatial", quietly = TRUE)) install.packages("ggspatial")
if (!requireNamespace("rosm", quietly = TRUE)) install.packages("rosm")
if (!requireNamespace("sf", quietly = TRUE)) install.packages("sf")


library(ggmap)
library(ggplot2)
library(ggspatial)
library(rosm)
library(sf)

Obtain a FREE stadia map key by creating an account on https://client.stadiamaps.com/dashboard/#/overview

Go to manage properties to create a new API key (https://docs.stadiamaps.com/tutorials/getting-started-in-r-with-ggmap/)

register_stadiamaps(key="d0072356-4b8c-4053-89e5-57e4b4439236", write =TRUE)

#write=TRUE so the key saves to your home directory and you don't need to reload each time

Now let’s obtain the actual sampling site data

#install.packages("googlesheets4")
library(googlesheets4)

BSB_metadate_url <- "https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1GA0ylVXwsdF5m9twDOkKwcYplBlBMXIfNep58dcXlXM/edit?usp=sharing"

Boat_data <- read_sheet(BSB_metadate_url, sheet = 'Boat', na = 'NA')

Define the bounding box for Gloucester

gloucester_bbox_1 <- c(left = -70.69, bottom = 42.64, right = -70.60, top = 42.7)

# zoomed in closer
gloucester_bbox_2 <- c(left = -70.69, bottom = 42.66, right = -70.64, top = 42.69)

Fetch the Stamen map tiles using ggmap

gloucester_map <- get_stadiamap(bbox = gloucester_bbox_1, zoom = 15, maptype = "stamen_toner")

gloucester_map_terrain <- get_stadiamap(bbox = gloucester_bbox_2, zoom = 15, maptype = "stamen_terrain")

you can change the resolution by playing with the Zoom. Higher values indicate higher resolution.

ggmap(gloucester_map) +
  geom_point(data = Boat_data, aes(x = `Longitude(DD)`, y = `Latitude(DD)`, color = Site_Name), size = 3) +
  #geom_text(data = Boat_data, aes(x = `Longitude(DD)`, y = `Latitude(DD)`, label = Site_Name), nudge_y = 0.01, color = "blue", size =3) +
  labs(title = "Map of Gloucester with Stamen Tiles", x = "Longitude", y = "Latitude") +
  #annotation_scale()+
  theme_minimal()

ggmap(gloucester_map_terrain) +
  geom_point(data = Boat_data, aes(x = `Longitude(DD)`, y = `Latitude(DD)`, shape = Site_Name), size = 3) +
  #geom_text(data = Boat_data, aes(x = `Longitude(DD)`, y = `Latitude(DD)`, label = Site_Name), nudge_y = 0.01, color = "blue", size =3) +
  labs(title = "", x = "Longitude", y = "Latitude") +
  theme_minimal()

Gloucester Map – zoomed out

Define the bounding box for Gloucester

gloucester_bbox_zoom_out <- c(left = -70.76, bottom = 42.56, right = -70.54, top = 42.72)

Fetch the Stamen map tiles using ggmap

#gloucester_map <- get_stadiamap(bbox = gloucester_bbox, zoom = 15, maptype = "stamen_toner")

gloucester_map_terrain_out <- get_stadiamap(bbox = gloucester_bbox_zoom_out, zoom = 14, maptype = "stamen_terrain")
## ℹ © Stadia Maps © Stamen Design © OpenMapTiles © OpenStreetMap contributors.
## ℹ 121 tiles needed, this may take a while (try a smaller zoom?)
gloucester_map_toner_out <- get_stadiamap(bbox = gloucester_bbox_zoom_out, zoom = 14, maptype = "stamen_toner")
## ℹ © Stadia Maps © Stamen Design © OpenMapTiles © OpenStreetMap contributors.
## ℹ 121 tiles needed, this may take a while (try a smaller zoom?)
ggmap(gloucester_map_toner_out) +
  geom_point(data = Boat_data, aes(x = `Longitude(DD)`, y = `Latitude(DD)`, color = Site_Name), size = 3) +
  #geom_text(data = Boat_data, aes(x = `Longitude(DD)`, y = `Latitude(DD)`, label = Site_Name), nudge_y = 0.01, color = "blue", size =3) +
  labs(title = "Gloucester_toner", x = "Longitude", y = "Latitude") +
  theme_minimal()

ggmap(gloucester_map_terrain_out) +
  geom_point(data = Boat_data, aes(x = `Longitude(DD)`, y = `Latitude(DD)`, color = Site_Name), size = 3) +
  geom_rect(aes(xmin = -70.69, xmax = -70.64, ymin = 42.66, ymax = 42.69), color= "blue",fill = NA, alpha = 0.4)+
  #geom_text(data = Boat_data, aes(x = `Longitude(DD)`, y = `Latitude(DD)`, label = Site_Name), nudge_y = 0.01, color = "blue", size =3) +
  labs(title = "Gloucester_terrain", x = "Longitude", y = "Latitude") +
  theme_minimal()
